  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "RK",
    "text": "This picture was taken January 17, 1995. It was 50 years after our liberation from the camps. My brother, Mark, decided that after 50 years we were all going to have a big celebration. He had a big party, and all the nephews and nieces, great-nephews, great-nieces, everybody was invited. This picture is my whole immediate family. I have my sons-- two sons and a daughter, two daughter-in-laws and a son-in-law and my seven grandchildren. There's another grandchild, which has-- has not-- was not born at the time, but now we have another little granddaughter.",
