  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "RK",
    "text": "These two women are very, very dear to me and dear to my whole family. One is my Auntie-- we used to call her Auntie Ethel, or [? Nima ?] Etta. And the other one is my grandma, my mother's mother. Her name was Sara Leah. And this picture was given to us by a aunt, who lived in America, which this picture was sent to her. Actually, she thought that the picture was my mother, but, unfortunately, it isn't. It's my aunt. We do not have any pictures of my mother at all, but we keep this picture very dear to our heart because she looks a little bit like my mom. [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS]",
